DataElementConcept.preferredName: Biospecimen Tracking Systematized Nomenclature of Medicine
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The act or process of following a person, animal, or object through space or time._A multiaxial, hierarchical classification system for diseases in man developed by the College of American Pathologists.
